<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/27419949-pixellle"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/27419949-pixellle">Pixellle</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">In addition to Revolution, there was a very good post-apocalyptic 2006 TV series called &quot;Jericho.&quot; It&apos;s about the people of a small town in Kansas, in<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">In addition to Revolution, there was a very good post-apocalyptic 2006 TV series called "Jericho." It's about the people of a small town in Kansas, in the aftermath of a limited nuclear attack on 23 major cities in the contiguous United States. They are totally cut off, and struggle to produce electricity, heat, food, shelter and medical care, and to deal with refugees. I thought it was a great mix of interesting characters and ideas, very well written. I recommend it.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
